How the Flow Actually Works
plain
Copy
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  STEP 1: User clicks SAVE                                               │
│  └── handleSave() called                                               │
│       └── Validation passes → isLoading = true                         │
│            └── updateRecord() → Opportunity updated                     │
│                 └── createCase() → Case created                         │
│                      └── createEmailMessage() → EmailMessage created   │
│                           └── Check: need OAuth?                        │
│                                ├── YES (no token/expired)              │
│                                │    └── openOAuthPopup()               │
│                                │         └── Opens /apex/OAuthCallbackHandler│
│                                │              └── VF redirects to /authorize │
│                                │                   └── User logs in      │
│                                │                        └── Salesforce redirects back to VF with ?code=xxx │
│                                │                             └── VF calls Apex exchangeCode() │
│                                │                                  └── Apex returns token │
│                                │                                       └── VF posts OAUTH_TOKEN to parent │
│                                │                                            └── handleOAuthMessage receives it │
│                                │                                                 └── Stores token │
│                                │                                                      └── Calls uploadAttachmentsViaRestApi() │
│                                │                                                           └── Loops attachments, uploads each │
│                                │                                                                └── Shows success toast │
│                                │                                                                     └── Closes modal │
│                                └── NO (have valid token)               │
│                                     └── Directly calls uploadAttachmentsViaRestApi() │
│                                          └── Same upload flow as above  │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
The Key Insight
handleOAuthMessage is not called immediately — it's an event listener. It waits for the popup to complete OAuth and post the message back. When that happens (could be seconds later), it receives the token and then calls the upload method.
Code Flow Visualization
JavaScript
Copy
// 1. SAVE clicked
async handleSave() {
    // ... validation, update record, create case, create email ...
    
    // 2. Check token
    if (!this.accessToken || this.isTokenExpired()) {
        this.openOAuthPopup();  // ← Opens popup, returns immediately
        // Code continues but doesn't call upload here
        // Upload happens LATER via handleOAuthMessage
        return; // Important: stops here, waits for popup
    }
    
    // 3. If we already have token, upload directly
    await this.uploadAttachmentsViaRestApi(...);
}

// 4. Popup completes OAuth, posts message
// 5. This fires asynchronously:
handleOAuthMessage = (event) => {
    if (event.data.type === 'OAUTH_TOKEN') {
        this.accessToken = event.data.accessToken;
        // 6. NOW upload starts:
        this.uploadAttachmentsViaRestApi(this.emailAttachments, this.pendingEmailId);
    }
};
Why It Works
Table
Question	Answer
How does upload start after popup?	handleOAuthMessage is called when popup posts message
Is the code blocked waiting?	No — it's event-driven, not blocking
What if popup is closed without auth?	OAUTH_ERROR message, shows error toast
Can user interact while popup open?	Yes, but modal stays open until upload completes
Your Working Code Summary
Table
File	Purpose
LWC JS	Opens popup, listens for token, uploads via REST
VF Page	Redirects to OAuth, exchanges code, posts token
Apex Controller	Exchanges auth code for access token
External Client App	Defines OAuth client, callback URL
For Production (Future Improvements)
Table
Improvement	How
Refresh token	Store in localStorage, reuse until expired
Parallel uploads	Use Promise.all() instead of sequential loop
Progress bar	Track uploadedCount / total in UI
Retry logic	Retry failed uploads individually
Error recovery	Allow retry without full re-auth

